{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"code":"GIOChannel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" data type aims to provide a portable method for"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"using file descriptors, pipes, and sockets, and integrating them"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"into the main event loop (see [struct","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"type":"text","text":"]). Currently,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"full support is available on UNIX platforms; support for Windows"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"is only partially complete."}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"struct","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"IOChannelRef","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"content":[{"level":2,"type":"heading","anchor":"overview","text":"Overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"GIOChannel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" on UNIX systems use"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.IOChannel.unix_new"},{"text":"]. This works for plain file descriptors,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"pipes and sockets. Alternatively, a channel can be created for a","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"file in a system independent manner using [ctor"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.IOChannel.new_file"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Once a ","type":"text"},{"code":"GIOChannel","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" has been created, it can be used in a generic"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"manner with the functions [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.IOChannel.read_chars"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.IOChannel.write_chars"},{"text":"], [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.IOChannel.seek_position","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"],","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"and [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.IOChannel.shutdown"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOChannel"},{"type":"text","text":" to the main event loop, use [func"},{"code":"GLib.io_add_watch","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"] or","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"code":"GLib.io_add_watch_full","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]. Here you specify which events you are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"interested in on the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOChannel"},{"type":"text","text":", and provide a function to be called"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"whenever these events occur."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GIOChannel"},{"text":" instances are created with an initial reference count of 1.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.IOChannel.ref","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] and [method"},{"code":"GLib.IOChannel.unref","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] can be used to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"increment or decrement the reference count respectively. When the"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"reference count falls to 0, the "},{"code":"GIOChannel","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is freed. (Though it","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"isn’t closed automatically, unless it was created using"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"[ctor","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.IOChannel.new_file","ty